## Five Sub-Packages Map (Explainability Dashboard)

| Module | May import from | May NOT import from |
|--------|-----------------|---------------------|
| `frontend-explainability/lib/wire/` | `zod`, stdlib | Everything else in `frontend-explainability/lib/` |
| `frontend-explainability/lib/ports/` | `wire/` | `adapters/`, `translators/`, `transport/`, `composition.ts` |
| `frontend-explainability/lib/translators/` | `wire/` | `adapters/`, `ports/`, `transport/`, `composition.ts`, any SDK |
| `frontend-explainability/lib/transport/` | `wire/`, stdlib, `EventSource` | `adapters/`, `ports/`, `translators/`, `composition.ts`, any SDK |
| `frontend-explainability/lib/adapters/` | `ports/`, `wire/`, third-party SDKs | `translators/`, `transport/`, `composition.ts`, other `adapters/` |
| `frontend-explainability/lib/composition.ts` | Everything in `frontend-explainability/lib/`, React context | Nothing imports composition |

Cross-project rule: `frontend-explainability/` MUST NEVER import from `frontend/`, `agent_ui_adapter/`, or any Python module.

## Layering Rules (F-Family)

- **F1** Composition root only. `process.env.*` reads for adapter wiring only in `frontend-explainability/lib/composition.ts`.
- **F2** Five sub-packages, no sixth. New top-level dir under `frontend-explainability/lib/` requires a merged ADR.
- **F3** Substrate swaps are composition-root-only.
- **F4** Frontend never imports backend Python at module scope. Cross-process boundary is HTTP/SSE only.

## Wire & Kernel Rules (W-Family)

- **W1** Pure shapes only. No I/O, no logging, no SDK calls in `wire/`.
- **W2** Mirror Python source of truth. Every `explainability_app/wire/` module has a TS twin under `frontend-explainability/lib/wire/`. Drift detected via `__python_schema_baseline__.json`.
- **W3** Discriminated unions, not bare unions.
- **W5** `trace_id` is structural where applicable.
- **W6** snake_case on the wire; camelCase only after a translator.
- **W7** Schema const + inferred type co-export with same name.

## Port Rules (P-Family)

- **P1** One interface per file.
- **P2** Vendor-neutral name.
- **P3** Behavioral contract documented in JSDoc above the interface.
- **P4** Typed errors declared via `@throws`.
- **P5** Async by default.
- **P6** No imports from `adapters/`, `translators/`, `transport/`, or `composition.ts`.
- **P7** Ports come paired with a conformance test.

## Adapter Rules (A-Family)

- **A1** SDK imports permitted only here.
- **A2** Adapters do not import each other.
- **A3** Depend on `ports/`, `wire/`, and SDKs only.
- **A4** SDK types never escape the adapter file. Convert to `wire/` shapes before returning.
- **A5** Error translation table in JSDoc (HTTP status -> typed port error).
- **A9** SDK pin in JSDoc (`@sdk <package> <version-spec>`).

## Translator Rules (T-Family)

- **T1** Imports only `wire/`. No SDK, no React, no I/O.
- **T2** Forward identifying fields from input to output.
- **T4** Table-driven Vitest tests co-located as `*.test.ts`; one test per discriminated-union variant.

## Transport Rules (X-Family)

- **X1** `EventSource` only in `frontend-explainability/lib/transport/sse_client.ts`.
- **X2** Zod-parse on receive; failures synthesize an error frame.
- **X4** Heartbeat detection thresholds (15s send / 30s detect).
- **X5** Backpressure: 100-event in-memory buffer; drop-oldest after that.

## Composition Rules (C-Family)

- **C1** Single profile switch — `process.env.*` reads only in composition root.
- **C2** Inject by port. Composition exports `buildAdapters()` returning a typed bag of port instances.
- **C5** Composition is the only file allowed to use `process.env.*` for adapter wiring.

## Browser Process Rules (B-Family)

- **B1** New components default to RSC. `'use client'` requires an inline justification comment.
- **B2** Pass Server Components to Client Components as `children`.
- **B3** Await `params`, `searchParams`, `cookies()`, `headers()` (Next 15 / React 19 contract).
- **B5** `cache: 'no-store'` is the default; `force-cache` only for non-user-scoped data.
- **B6** Route Handlers are composition adapters — no business `if/else`.

## UI Rules (U-Family)

- **U1** RSC by default.
- **U2** Leaf `'use client'`. Push the boundary as far down the tree as possible.
- **U4** ARIA live region for streaming content: `<div role="log" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="false">`. Never `assertive`.
- **U6** `cn()` (`clsx` + `tailwind-merge`) for class merging. Template-string conditionals forbidden.
- **U7** shadcn primitives over custom-built.
- **U8** Design tokens via Tailwind v4 `@theme` blocks in `app/globals.css`.

## Frontend Architectural Invariants (F-R1..F-R4)

- **F-R1** No domain logic in React components.
- **F-R2** SDK imports allowed only in `adapters/`.
- **F-R3** One interface per `ports/` module.
- **F-R4** Route Handlers are composition adapters, not business logic.

Note: F-R5 (prompts in `.j2`) is vacuous — this dashboard has no prompts. F-R6/F-R7 are vacuous — the browser only forwards backend-generated identifiers; it never generates `trace_id` or `event_id`. F-R9 is interpreted as "the dashboard backend is the only process that touches the filesystem; the browser never reads `cache/`/`logs/`".

## Anti-Patterns (Applicable Subset)

| ID | Name | AUTO-REJECT |
|----|------|-------------|
| FE-AP-7 | Generating `trace_id` in the browser (breaks trust propagation) | **YES** |
| FE-AP-9 | `console.*` outside an adapter | no |
| FE-AP-11 | `'use client'` on the root layout | no |
| FE-AP-12 | `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` of agent output (XSS-critical) | **YES** |
| FE-AP-13 | Direct SDK import outside `adapters/` | no |
| FE-AP-14 | Schema drift: TS Zod with no matching Python baseline entry | no |
| FE-AP-15 | Adapter without an error-translation table | no |
| FE-AP-16 | Port without a conformance test | no |
| FE-AP-17 | Translator that touches `localStorage` / `fetch` / `document` | no |
| FE-AP-18 | API URL holding a cloud credential | **YES** |
| FE-AP-19 | Adding `'unsafe-inline'` to CSP | **YES** |

**Dropped (not applicable to this MVP):**
- FE-AP-4 (`useComponent` iframe without `sandbox`) — no generative-UI iframes in this dashboard.
- FE-AP-6 (mutating a sealed envelope) — no sealed envelopes / HITL flows.
- FE-AP-20 (CopilotKit barrel import) — CopilotKit not in the SDK allowlist.

## Security Hardening Quick Reference

- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` on any agent-derived or backend-fetched content.
- No browser-side `trace_id` generation (`crypto.randomUUID()`, `nanoid()`, etc.).
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` env vars must not match `*KEY*`, `*SECRET*`, `*TOKEN*`, `*PRIVATE*`, `*CREDENTIAL*`.
- API URL in composition root only — never hardcoded in adapters or components.

## Accessibility Quick Reference (WCAG 2.2 AA)

**Auto-checkable:**
- ARIA role validity, required/prohibited attributes.
- Form inputs have associated `<label>` or `aria-label`.
- Interactive elements: `<button>`/`<a>` not `<div onClick>`.
- `aria-live` attribute presence and syntactic validity.
- Image `alt` attributes.

**Manual / gap territory (record as `gaps`, never as findings):**
- Announcement timing, focus preservation, reading order, color contrast, screen-reader UX quality.

## Performance Quick Reference

- `next/image` for every content image. `<img>` fails review.
- `cache: 'no-store'` on every user-scoped route.
- `<Suspense>` boundaries around every async server boundary.
- Heavy chart libraries (`recharts`, `@visx/*`, `reactflow`) on non-first-paint routes use `next/dynamic`.

## Testing Pyramid

| Layer | Tool | Required when |
|-------|------|---------------|
| Unit -- pure | Vitest | Any new translator, wire schema, pure helper |
| Unit -- component | Vitest + React Testing Library | Any new component |
| Integration -- adapter | Vitest + MSW | Any new adapter |
| Port conformance | Vitest parametrized | Any new port or adapter |
| Architecture -- TS layering | `ts-morph` walker | Always runs |
| Wire schema drift | Python baseline diff | On any `frontend-explainability/lib/wire/` change |
| Accessibility -- static | `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y` | Always runs in CI |

**Failure paths first:** rejection tests (404/500/timeout/parse-error) before happy-path tests for every adapter.

**No live LLM calls in CI.**

**`tsc --noEmit` clean.** Type errors block merge.

